  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In our [Dockerfile](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/Dockerfile), `make geth` does not inject the commit hash into Geth's version string because the `.git` repository is ignored via [.dockerignore](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/.dockerignore).\r\n\r\nWould help to figure out which files from `.git` should be forwarded into the docker build process to re-enable the commit hashes in the version string. A good starter is [`build.LocalEnv`](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/internal/build/env.go#L83), which tries to pull the commit hash from git.\r\n\r\nYou can also read the discussion in https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/15351 for the proposal of a good solution (the PR itself wasn't suitable).",
